## 1. Overview
This section explains the high-level architecture of ProtectWave VPN and how the client, backend, and servers interact to provide secure internet access.

## 2. Components

### Client
- Installed on mobile or desktop devices  
- Handles login, server selection, connect/disconnect, and connection status  

### Backend
- Manages accounts and authentication  
- Issues tokens for secure login  
- Does not handle user internet traffic  

### VPN Servers
- Handles encrypted traffic using WireGuard  
- Routes internet traffic securely  
- Ensures privacy and anonymity  

## 3. System Flow
[Client / User Device]
|
v
[Backend Server] --> authentication, account management
|
v
[VPN Servers] --> encrypt and route user traffic
|
v
Internet

## 4. Security Considerations
- User data isolation  
- Encrypted passwords  
- Secure VPN traffic via WireGuard

